PN,44303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1781190689
OL,3,CSir Jeffrey Donaldson takes to stand
OL,4,Cin sex abuse trial
OL,6,FDefence barrister Kieran Vaughan KC
OL,7,Fcalled Donaldson as a witness in the
OL,8,Ftrial at Newry Crown Court shortly
OL,9,Fafter 10.30am on Thursday.
OL,11,FWearing a blue suit and red tie, he
OL,12,Fwas sworn in after entering the
OL,13,Fwitness box and confirmed his identity.
OL,15,FHe told the jury he had developed an
OL,16,Finterest in politics at the age of 18
OL,17,Fand was first elected to the Northern
OL,18,FIreland Assembly at the age of 22.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1781190689
OL,3,CSir Jeffrey Donaldson takes to stand
OL,4,Cin sex abuse trial
OL,6,FHe said he was first elected to
OL,7,FParliament in 1997 and had been
OL,8,Finvolved in negotiations before the
OL,9,Fsigning of the Good Friday Agreement
OL,10,Fin 1998.
OL,12,FMr Vaughan asked him if he accepted
OL,13,Fany of the allegations made by
OL,14,FComplainant B, the older of the two
OL,15,Falleged victims.
OL,17,FDonaldson said: "No."
OL,19,FThe barrister asked the same question
OL,20,Fabout allegations made by Complainant
OL,21,FA, and Donaldson again said "no".
OL,26,@yD@QOUyD@UO]}D@]OU}D@`O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/12
