PN,44311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1781190689
OL,3,CSir Jeffrey Donaldson takes to stand
OL,4,Cin sex abuse trial
OL,6,FHe was asked if he had been
OL,7,Fapologising for abuse.
OL,9,FDonaldson said: "No, because there had
OL,10,Fbeen no abuse and that was not the
OL,11,Fnature of the meeting."
OL,13,FThe barrister then turned to
OL,14,Fallegations made by Complainant A.
OL,16,FAsked if he had ever kissed her on the
OL,17,Fmouth as a child, Donaldson said: "Why
OL,18,Fwould I kiss a child using my tongue?
OL,20,F"That is just ridiculous, that just
OL,21,Fdid not ever happen."
OL,26,@qD@QOUsD@WO]yD@cOU|D@AOU}D@UO]
